<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="39" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="14.[132,776,1133,1289]" pageId="14" pageNumber="39">
REMARK. — Reported for W National Park (
<bibRefCitation author="BALANCA G. &amp; CORNELIS D. &amp; WILSON R." box="[574,761,1133,1157]" pageId="14" pageNumber="39" refId="ref64925" refString="BALANCA G., CORNELIS D. &amp; WILSON R. 2007. - Les oiseaux du complexe WAP. ECOPAS. Cirad, Montpellier." type="book" year="2007">
Balanca 
<emphasis box="[656,704,1133,1157]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="39">et al.</emphasis>
2007
</bibRefCitation>
), but not further considered as present in 
<collectingCountry box="[525,656,1159,1183]" name="Burkina Faso" pageId="14" pageNumber="39">Burkina Faso</collectingCountry>
. The species has a mainly western and southern African distribution, but in 2018 a colony was unexpectedly found and carefully documented in northern 
<collectingCountry box="[254,327,1239,1263]" name="Senegal" pageId="14" pageNumber="39">Senegal</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="PIOT B. &amp; BACUEZ F." box="[342,545,1239,1263]" pageId="14" pageNumber="39" pagination="206 - 212" refId="ref68224" refString="PIOT B. &amp; BACUEZ F. 2021. - A major range extension of Horus Swift Apus horus, north-west to Senegal. Bulletin of the African Bird Club 28: 206 - 212." type="journal article" year="2021">Piot &amp; Bacuez 2021</bibRefCitation>
), so further research in 
<collectingCountry box="[132,260,1265,1289]" name="Burkina Faso" pageId="14" pageNumber="39">Burkina Faso</collectingCountry>
are warranted.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
